    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-19T18:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-19T18:41:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/10–1951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassies in Turkey and Greece</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d325fn1">Message drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MCR1"
                            >Moore</persName> of <gloss target="#t_GTI1">GTI</gloss> and cleared
                        with <gloss target="#t_RA1">RA</gloss> and the Office of the Assistant
                        Secretary of State for Congressional Affairs. It was sent to Ankara as 354
                        and Athens as 1904. It was repeated to London for <persName
                            corresp="#p_SCM1">Spofford</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-19T18:41:00-05:00"
                            >October 19, 1951—6:41 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss> Greek-Turkish Protocol opened for signature
                    London at US request on Oct 17 and signed that day by <gloss target="#t_Dep1"
                        >Dep</gloss>s representing US, UK, Belg, Canad, Ice, Neth, Port, Nor.
                    Remaining four countries expected sign Oct 22. However, in view anticipated
                    adjournment Cong tomorrow Protocol not submitted to Senate. If adjournment
                    delayed there remains slight possibility submission but prospects not
                    favorable.</p>
                <p>If Cong adjourns tomorrow you may in your discretion express to <gloss
                        target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> Dept’s regrets that due to adjournment of
                    Sen Protocol cld not be submitted for action at this session. You may also
                    indicate that US made special arrangements to sign Protocol Oct 17, without
                    waiting for several other countries which had not yet completed parliamentary
                    and other requirements, in order be prepared take advantage remote possibility
                    that Sen wld remain in session long enough enable action be taken on Protocol.
                    Dept will, of course, work actively for early Senate action after Cong
                    reconvenes Jan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
